{"t":"2026-06-29T15:44:28.210Z","tool":"schedule_task","args":{"prompt":"Run exactly this with run_shell and report its output: curl -s 'https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd' | jq -r .bitcoin.usd. Then, if the fetch is successful, call post_to_chat with the current UTC time, the price, and 'WOOHOO!' if the price is >= 59183.21, otherwise 'OH NO!'. If the fetch fails or returns empty/null, post_to_chat that the Bitcoin price fetch failed.","every_seconds":300,"label":"Monitor Bitcoin Price"},"status":"ok","ms":2}
{"t":"2026-06-29T15:45:32.143Z","tool":"schedule_task","args":{"prompt":"Run exactly this with run_shell and report its output: curl -s 'https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd' | jq -r .bitcoin.usd\n\nThen call post_to_chat ONCE with a single short line containing: the current UTC time, 'BTC $<price>', and 'WOOHOO!' if the price is >= 59183.21 otherwise 'OH NO!'. Use ONLY the real fetched price. If the fetch fails or returns empty/null, post_to_chat that the Bitcoin price fetch failed — do not invent a price.","every_seconds":300,"label":"Monitor Bitcoin Price"},"status":"ok","ms":1}
{"t":"2026-06-29T15:46:39.022Z","tool":"schedule_task","args":{"prompt":"Run exactly this with run_shell and report its output: curl -s 'https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd' | jq -r .bitcoin.usd; if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then price=$(curl -s 'https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd' | jq -r .bitcoin.usd); if [ -z \"$price\" ]; then echo 'Bitcoin price fetch failed'; else current_time=$(date -u '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'); if (( $(echo \"$price >= 59183.21\" | bc -l) )); then echo \"$current_time BTC \\\\$${price} WOOHOO!\"; else echo \"$current_time BTC \\\\$${price} OH NO!\"; fi; fi; else echo 'Bitcoin price fetch failed'; fi","every_seconds":300,"label":"Monitor Bitcoin Price"},"status":"ok","ms":1}
{"t":"2026-06-29T15:47:48.904Z","tool":"schedule_task","args":{"prompt":"Run exactly this with run_shell and report its output: curl -s 'https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd' | jq -r .bitcoin.usd; if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then price=$(curl -s 'https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd' | jq -r .bitcoin.usd); if [ -z \"$price\" ]; then post_to_chat('Bitcoin price fetch failed.'); else current_time=$(date -u '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'); if (( $(echo \"$price >= 59183.21\" | bc -l) )); then post_to_chat(\"$current_time BTC \\\\$${price} WOOHOO!\"); else post_to_chat(\"$current_time BTC \\\\$${price} OH NO!\"); fi; fi; else post_to_chat('Bitcoin price fetch failed.'); fi","every_seconds":300,"label":"Monitor Bitcoin Price"},"status":"ok","ms":2}
